{"id":"discord-bot-test-suite-t0n","title":"Add docs/GOAL.md (North Star requirements)","description":"Create docs/GOAL.md as the single source-of-truth for what this repo is building.\n\nIt must include:\n- goal: benchmark Cloud Run cold-start across many language/framework implementations\n- request flow: Discord interactions webhook -\u003e validate signature -\u003e Ping/Pong OR publish sanitized message to Pub/Sub -\u003e deferred response\n- key fixed decisions:\n  - support Ping (type=1) -\u003e Pong (type=1) and do NOT publish\n  - support Slash command (type=2) -\u003e deferred response type=5 (non-ephemeral) and publish to Pub/Sub\n  - Pub/Sub emulator supported; per-test unique topic/sub names\n  - redact sensitive fields from logs and Pub/Sub messages (token, signature material, raw body)\n  - golden contract test suite in Go; black-box container testing\n  - versions should be modern but not bleeding edge\n  - phased approach: local-only first, then Cloud Run+Cloud Logging for one service, then roll out\n- language/framework matrix list (include Go gin, Python django, PHP laravel, Ruby rails, C++ drogon, etc.)\n- acceptance criteria for MVP and full build\n- explicit non-goals\n\nDefinition of Done:\n- docs/GOAL.md exists\n- clear, concise, agent-friendly (1-2 pages)\n- no contradictions with docs/CONTRACT.md / SECURITY / OBSERVABILITY","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"github@pmgledhill.com","created_at":"2026-01-20T10:09:01.940993Z","created_by":"Paul Gledhill","updated_at":"2026-01-20T13:29:54.431628Z","closed_at":"2026-01-20T13:29:54.431628Z","close_reason":"Closed","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"discord-bot-test-suite-t0n","depends_on_id":"discord-bot-test-suite-c5k","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-20T11:14:02.512468Z","created_by":"Paul Gledhill"}]}
{"id":"discord-bot-test-suite-v7j","title":"Restructure GitHub Actions: main lint workflow + per-service workflows","description":"Restructure CI workflows for better separation of concerns:\n\n## Main Lint Workflow\n- Lint GitHub Actions files (actionlint)\n- Lint Markdown files (markdownlint)\n- Lint YAML/JSON files (prettier)\n- Validate pre-commit config\n- Runs on changes to: .github/**, *.md, *.yml, *.json\n\n## Per-Service Workflows\nCreate separate workflow per service that:\n- Only triggers when that service's folder changes\n- Runs language-specific linting (golangci-lint, flake8, eslint, etc.)\n- Builds the service container\n- Runs contract tests against that service\n- Completely isolated from other services\n\n## File Structure\n```\n.github/workflows/\n├── lint.yml                    # Main generic linting\n├── service-go-gin.yml          # Go/Gin service CI\n├── service-python-django.yml   # Django service CI (when implemented)\n├── service-python-flask.yml    # Flask service CI (when implemented)\n└── ...\n```\n\n## Benefits\n- Parallel development of services\n- Faster CI (only affected service runs)\n- Clear ownership per service\n- Language-specific tooling per workflow\n\n## Tasks\n1. Create main lint.yml workflow\n2. Refactor contract-tests.yml → service-go-gin.yml\n3. Add golangci-lint to Go workflow\n4. Document workflow pattern for future services\n\nDefinition of Done:\n- Main lint workflow passing\n- Go/Gin service workflow passing with language-specific linting\n- Old contract-tests.yml removed or refactored\n- Pattern documented for adding new service workflows","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"github@pmgledhill.com","created_at":"2026-01-20T14:27:52.311836Z","created_by":"Paul Gledhill","updated_at":"2026-01-20T14:33:13.924634Z","closed_at":"2026-01-20T14:33:13.924634Z","close_reason":"Closed"}
